the primary settlement in town, where 1,688 people resided at the 2010 census, is defined by the u.s. census bureau as the bristol census-designated place (cdp) and is located at the intersection of   routes 3a and 104. the town was incorporated in 1819. extensive deposits of fine sand or clay similar to the "bristol sand" used in bristol, england to make fine china and pottery gave the town its name.